# Multi-Tenant Isolation

Use when writing queries, APIs, services, or repository logic in a multi-company context.

## Required invariants
- ALWAYS scope data by tenant/company (typically `companyId`) in:
  - database models (composite keys / tenant columns)
  - queries and filters (`WHERE` must include the tenant key)
- NEVER read/mutate tenant-owned rows without that tenant filter.
- Every request must assume a resolved tenant context (from JWT/session or explicit param after validation).

## Validation requirements
- Validate authenticated user belongs to that tenant/company.
- Validate the target resource belongs to that tenant/company (IDs alone are not sufficient).

## Enforcement point
- Apply isolation consistently in controllers, services, and repositories (not only one layer).
